      <PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>THE PURPOSE OF CASTELLA CARES, THE SOPHIA VALSAMOS FOUNDATION, IS TO USE ALL AVAILABLE RESOURCES, TO ASSIST TODAY'S LONG ISLAND YOUTH TO ENSURE THAT NO CHILD IS LIMITED OR PREVENTED FROM ACHIEVING THEIR DREAMS OR LIFETIME ASPIRATIONS. THE FOUNDATION ACHIEVES THEIR OBJECTIVES THROUGH COMMUNITY AWARENESS, PROVIDING ACCESS TO COUNSELING, LIFE SKILL TRAINING, OPEN COMMUNICATIONS AND OTHER CREATIVE OUTLETS. IN ADDITION, CASTELLA CARESPROVIDES HUMANITARIAN EFFORTS TO THE LONG ISLAND COMMUNITY BY FIGHTING HUNGER, AND PROVIDING HOLIDAY JOY TO CHILDREN IN NEED.</PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>THE ORGANIZATION WAS PROUD TO SPONSOR THE OH, SHIFT WORKSHOP FOR TEENS WHICH WAS GIVEN VIRTUALLY TO TEENS AT BOTH MIDDLE-SCHOOL AND HIGH-SCHOOL LEVEL IN MULTIPLE SCHOOL DISTRICTS. OVER THE COURSE OF MULTIPLE SESSIONS, THE TEENS AND THEIR EMPOWERMENT COACH ENGAGED IN VARIOUS INTERACTIVE DISCUSSIONS AND ACTIVITIES TO BECOME MORE SELF-AWARE, CONFIDENT, AND ABLE TO MANAGE THEIR REACTIONS TO VARIOUS SITUATIONS IN A POSITIVE MANNER. THE OH, SHIFT WORKSHOP WAS ALSO DELIVERED TO 150 CAMPERS AT CAMP NAH-JEE WAH IN PENNSYLVANIA.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
